This paper deals with type systems and polymorphism, which are central topics in programming languages (cs.PL). The paper specifically focuses on subtyping, which is a key concept in type systems and is often studied in the context of programming languages (cs.TYPES). The paper also discusses the use of type constraints and unification, which are common techniques in type systems and programming languages (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the encoding of subtyping hierarchies, which is a topic that is often studied in the context of software engineering (cs.SE) and compiler design (cs.CL).
